e\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"REUTERS\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}, {\"begin\": 497, \"end\": 509, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Simone Biles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\"}, {\"begin\": 602, \"end\": 610, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999700301871552, \"rank\": 2.9632518043709242e-05, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The new skill is a clear hip circle forward with 1.5 turns to handstand, a variation of an element named for Canadian Wilhelm Weiler, which Biles has performed for much of her career, the International Gymnastics Federation (FIG) said.\", \"from\": 696, \"to\": 931, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 805, \"end\": 813, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"score\": 0.9971577824978843, \"rank\": 0.0028479022014772405, \"text\": \"Canadian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\"}, {\"begin\": 884, \"end\": 925, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Gymnastics_Federation\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Gymnastics Federation (FIG)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Gymnastics_Federation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Gymnastics_Federation\"}, {\"begin\": 884, \"end\": 925, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Gymnastics_Federation\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Gymnastics Federation (FIG)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Gymnastics_Federation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Gymnastics_Federation\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"FIG's technical committee awarded it a difficulty value of E on a scale from A to J, meaning it is worth 0.5 in difficulty.\", \"from\": 933, \"to\": 1056, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 933, \"end\": 936, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Gymnastics_Federation\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.8963640637829355e-46, \"text\": \"FIG\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Gymnastics_Federation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Gymnastics_Federation\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The four-time Olympic champion already has five elements named after her including two vaults, two tumbling skills on floor exercise and a dismount on balance beam.\", \"from\": 1058, \"to\": 1222, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Only Nellie Kim, the retired Soviet and Belarusian five-time Olympic gold medallist, has more skills named after her, with seven.\", \"from\": 1224, \"to\": 1353, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1229, \"end\": 1239, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nellie_Kim\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nellie Kim\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nellie_Kim\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nellie_Kim\"}, {\"begin\": 1253, \"end\": 1259, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Soviet_Union\", \"score\": 0.9999919998021471, \"rank\": 7.993778777416622e-06, \"text\": \"Soviet\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Soviet_Union\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Soviet_Union\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Biles is the fourth woman aimi